frameDefinitions: A Cook applies heat to Food, where the Temperature_setting of the heat and Duration of application may be specified.

Because it no longer functions adequately under the given circumstances, an Agent (or non-Agentive Cause) undertakes steps to change the structural makeup of a complex Entity with interdependent parts, for instance an institution or a system of laws.
An Entity (generally food) is exposed to a Heat_source whose Temperature may also be specified.
An Assailant physically attacks a Victim (which is usually but not always sentient), causing or intending to cause the Victim physical damage.
A Figure is located essentially at the same location as a Ground, which is viewed as point-like, or having no important internal or external structure.
A Vehicle moves into position or otherwise changes configuration or state as preparation for normal operation.
frameExamples: They want to <t>reform</t> the law on Sunday trading.
Bacon was <t>frying</t> in the pan, and a great heap of eggs already lay steaming on a plate.
As soon as he stepped out of the bar he was <t>set</t> upon by four men in ski-masks.
The flight for New York finally <t>lifted off</t> from Oakland International with one hundred passengers aboard.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Cook</fen> applies heat to the <fen>Food</fen>.
This role identifes the entity that  directly supplies heat to the <fen>Food</fen>.
<fen>Food</fen> is the entity to which heat is applied by the <fen>Cook</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Temperature_setting</fen> of the <fen>Heating_instrument</fen> for the <fen>Food</fen>.
The <fen>Container</fen> holds the <fen>Food</fen> to which heat is applied.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> at which the heat application occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the heat application  occurs.
The sentient entity that effects a change in the <fen>Entity</fen>.

This role denotes a complex, abstract, human-created entity with interdependent parts which has either deteriorated or is no longer adequate for its purpose given a change in circumstances and which the <fen>Agent</fen> therefore wants to modify.
This role is for non-human causes, such as a processes or institutions, responsible for reform.
The time at which the change of the <fen>Entity</fen> is caused.
The place where the reformation occurs.
The <fen>Entity</fen> (often a food item)  that absorbs heat.
The <fen>Container</fen> that holds the <fen>Entity</fen> that absorbs the heat.
This role identifies the object that directly supplies heat to the <fen>Entity</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the heat absorption takes place.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the heat application occurs.
This role is the being or entity that is injured by the <fen>Assailant</fen>'s attack.
The person (or other self-directed entity) that is attempting physical harm to the <fen>Victim</fen>.
This role identifies the time when the <fen>Assailant</fen> attacks the <fen>Victim</fen>.
This role identifies the place where the <fen>Assailant</fen> makes an assault on the <fen>Victim</fen>.
The <fen>Ground</fen> serves as a basis for describing the location of the <fen>Figure</fen>.
The <fen>Figure</fen> is perceived as located relative to a certain <fen>Ground</fen> location. The <fen>Figure</fen> can be an entity or an event.
The period of time during which the locative relation between <fen>Figure</fen> and <fen>Ground</fen> obtains.
The vehicle which moves into position for typical operation.
Any expression which describes the location that the <fen>Vehicle</fen> has been stationed at.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Vehicle</fen> gets ready for motion.
The <fen>Place</fen> describes the location where the <fen>Vehicle</fen> prepares for motion.
